      "formatted_context": "=== TASK ===\nFix refund bug for UPI payment.\n\n=== RULES ===\n- (code.inspect_failing_test_first) Inspect the failing test first to understand expected behavior.\n- (code.include_relevant_source) Include the source files relevant to the failure.\n- (code.include_stack_trace) Include the stack trace pointing at the failing line.\n- (code.exclude_unrelated_files) Do not include files unrelated to the failure.\n- (code.preserve_public_api) Preserve the public API; do not change function signatures.\n- (code.prefer_smallest_patch) Prefer the smallest patch that fixes the failing test.\n\n=== EVIDENCE ===\n[refund.py] refund.py\ndef process_refund(payment):\n    # BUG: UPI refunds must use the vpa, not card_last4\n    if payment.method == 'upi':\n        return issue_refund(payment.card_last4, payment.amount)\n    return issue_refund(payment.account_id, payment.amount)\n\ndef issue_refund(destination, amount):\n    return {'destination': destination, 'amount': amount, 'status': 'ok'}\n\n[test_refund.py] test_refund.py\ndef test_upi_refund_uses_vpa():\n    p = Payment('upi', 100, vpa='alice@bank')\n    result = process_refund(p)\n    assert result['destination'] == 'alice@bank'  # FAILS: got None\n\n[stack_trace.log] stack_trace.log\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"refund.py\", line 4, in process_refund\n    return issue_refund(payment.card_last4, payment.amount)\nAssertionError: UPI refund destination was None, expected 'alice@bank'\n\n[payment.py] payment.py\nclass Payment:\n    def __init__(self, method, amount, account_id=None, vpa=None, card_last4=None):\n        self.method = method\n        self.amount = amount\n        self.account_id = account_id\n        self.vpa = vpa\n        self.card_last4 = card_last4\n",
